# Testing

## Test runners and configs

- Vitest is configured via app/vitest.config.ts and variants (coverage, crypto). TZ=UTC enforced in scripts
- Playwright E2E: app/playwright.config.ts, with projects chromium-public/authed and optional mobile/webkit configs in scripts

## Test suites (examples)

- Unit/integration under:
  - app/server/api/__tests__ — endpoint tests grouped by domain (auth, account, register, reoccurrence, budget, reports, notifications, tasks, health)
  - app/server/services/__tests__ — Plaid, RSA/JWT/Hash services, forecast services
  - app/lib/__tests__ — rounding, utils, category filters
  - app/schema/__tests__ — Zod schemas
  - app/stores/__tests__ — Pinia stores
  - app/pages/__tests__ — Page-level behavior (e.g., login)
- Forecast engine
  - app/server/services/forecast/__tests__ — unit/integration/regression tests with snapshots and helper runner (test-runner.ts)
- E2E (Playwright)
  - app/tests/e2e/specs — public/authed specs + accessibility and visual snapshot baselines
  - app/tests/e2e/setup — global setup/teardown, auth helpers

## Commands

- pnpm test — run Vitest
- pnpm test:coverage — generate V8 coverage (used in Sonar workflow)
- pnpm test:crypto — crypto-intensive tests
- Forecast:
  - pnpm test:forecast, :unit, :integration, :performance, :all
- E2E:
  - pnpm test:e2e (chromium public + authed)
  - pnpm test:e2e:update-snapshots (local)
  - Staging snapshots via GitHub workflow e2e-update-staging-snapshots.yml

## CI considerations

- CI sets minimal env and runs prisma generate before tests
- Database is not required for most tests; mocks in place. Some suites use generated Prisma client
- Snapshot images differ across OS; Linux baselines updated via staging workflow

## Adding tests

- For API changes: add/extend tests under app/server/api/__tests__ with success/failure cases
- For services: provide unit tests co-located in __tests__ directories
- For forecast logic: add targeted unit/integration and update regression snapshots carefully
- For E2E flows: cover primary user journeys (login, profile, budgets, registers, reoccurrences, reports)

